issue.title: [25.0] Update dependencies, make httpx required dependency
issue.body:
missing httpx (required for proxy introduced in https://github.com/galaxyproject/galaxy/pull/20054) breaks planemo for release branches, since we don't install dev dependencies there.
Also does a final dependency update, since we haven't merged one in the last 3 weeks and at least the pydantic update looks important.

@homeworkprod @cbini  the query shown to produce the error verbatim produces no error for me here.   Can I please have information regarding the full version of PostgreSQL in use ?   Is this PostgreSQL or a third party variant ?
I've seen a similar error with psycopg2 and PostgreSQL 9.6.
OK so a very old PG version, which is what I'm suspecting here also

based on the query @cbini  illustrated and looking at the code in https://gerrit.sqlalchemy.org/c/sqlalchemy/sqlalchemy/+/5818/2/lib/sqlalchemy/dialects/postgresql/base.py , we would deduce that particular PG is >=11 and less than 15.  

12 seems to be the oldest I can get running easily and the query as written doesn't fail, not sure if it's actual data in the rows that causes the fail
